ENERGY Minister, Dr Medard Kalemani, yesterday directed Derm Electrics Tanzania who won a tender to supply electricity to peri urban areas in Kigamboni District in Dar es Salaam to make sure electricity is connected to customers within seven days from the time payment is completed. The directive was given yesterday during the launch of the third phase of Rural Energy Agency (REA), project at the Kibamande grounds in Mwasonga ward, Kigamboni District, which is set to supply electricity to the remaining 36 streets that did not have electricity at a cost of 9.34/-billion. “These instructions are not for Kigamboni alone, but directed to contractors, engineers and all managers across the country. The time of installing electricity is within seven days from the day the customer completes payment,” he emphasized